title: 661-F
statement: F. Primes in Intervaltime limit per test2 secondsmemory limit per test64 megabytesinputstandard inputoutputstandard outputYou are given two integersaandb(a≤b). How many prime numbers are there on the interval fromatob, inclusive?InputThe input contains two integersaandb(2 ≤a≤b≤ 1 000 000), separated by a single space.OutputOutput a single integer — the number of primes betweenaandb, inclusive.ExamplesInput10 20Output4Input23 23Output1Input271 566Output46

processed.result: You are given two numbers, $a$ and $b$ ($2 \le a \le b \le 1,000,000$).  Count how many prime numbers are between $a$ and $b$, including both $a$ and $b$.
Count the number of prime numbers between two given numbers.
